itory Canon\n\u003e\nArchive\n\u003e\nNotebookLM\n\n---\n\n## Migration Safeguards\n\nThe following failures have already been observed in the historical repository:\n\n- Noah occupation drift\n- Douglas-Bloodmoon naming drift\n- Family relationship degradation\n- World canonical compression\n- Character role homogenization\n\nThe rebuild must prevent recurrence.\n\nEvery imported element must be auditable back to:\n\nSource\n→ Audit\n→ Decision\n→ Implementation\n\n---\n\n## Initial Rebuild Objective\n\nThe goal of the new repository is not content quantity.\n\nThe goal is:\n\nRecover and stabilize canon before expansion.\n\nNo archived world, character, engine, lorebook, experience, or storyline may be imported until its canonical form has been verified through the Canon Recovery Workflow.\n\n---\n\n# Phase 1 Deliverable\n\nCreate only the repository skeleton.\n\nNo runtime logic.\n\nNo lore.\n\nNo world data.\n\nNo family graph.\n\nNo experiences.\n\nNo character definitions.\n\nNo state logic.\n\nNo relationship logic.\n\nNo migrations.\n\n---\n\n# Required Structure\n\nSvartulfrVerse/\n\nREADME.md\n\ncore/\n│\n├── ADR-000_Runtime_Baseline.md\n├── Architecture.md\n├── Repository_Scope.md\n└── Rebuild_Principles.md\n\nengines/\n│\n├── En_Core.js\n├── relationship_engine.js\n├── state_engine.js\n├── family_engine.js\n└── README.md\n\n---\n\n# README.md\n\nDescribe:\n\n- repository purpose\n- current scope\n- rebuild status\n\nCurrent status:\n\nBootstrap Phase\n\n---\n\n# ADR-000_Runtime_Baseline.md\n\nRecord the decision:\n\nLegacy Repository:\nProgetti\n\nRole:\nHistorical Archive\n\nNew Repository:\nSvartulfrVerse\n\nRole:\nActive Runtime Canon Repository\n\nDocument:\n\n- freeze decision\n- rebuild decision\n- runtime-first approach\n- future world reintroduction policy\n\nNo implementation details.\n\n---\n\n# Architecture.md\n\nDocument:\n\nCore Principles:\n\n- Runtime First\n- Preserve Behavior Before Refactoring\n- Knowledge vs Behavior Separation\n- Character Canonicality\n- Incremental Reintroduction\n- Canonical Stabilization\n\nDocument current scope:\n\n- Only Human\n- Contemporary\n- Los Angeles Dynasty\n\nDocument current validation paradigm:\n\nLA_OnlyHuman_Academic_Timeline\n\nPrinciple:\n\nCharacter age, education and occupation must form a plausible real-world timeline.\n\nExamples:\n\n19 → Freshman / Sophomore\n22-23 → Bachelor Graduate\n25 → 3L Law Student / Graduate Student / Early Career Professional\n28 → PhD Candidate / Resident / Early Management\n31+ → Marriage / Children\n\nPurpose:\n\nPrevent migration drift toward unrealistic prodigy careers and preserve contemporary realism.\n\n---\n\n# Repository_Scope.md\n\nExplicitly document:\n\nSupported:\n\n- Only Human\n- Contemporary\n- Los Angeles Dynasty\n\nNot Supported:\n\n- Urban Fantasy\n- Cyber\n- Fantasy\n- Norse Mythic\n- Wasteland\n- Regency\n\n---\n\n# Rebuild_Principles.md\n\nDocument:\n\n1. Archive First\n2. Runtime Validation Before Expansion\n3. Single Source of Truth\n4. Preserve Historical Evidence\n5. No Migration Without Audit\n6. Canon Before Optimization\n7. Runtime Before Architecture\n8. Family Authority Before Expansion\n\n---\n\n# Engine Layer\n\nImportant:\n\nCreate engine shells only.\n\nNo logic.\n\nNo implementation.\n\nNo migration.\n\nNo copied code.\n\nNo runtime behavior.\n\n---\n\n## En_Core.js\n\nPlaceholder only.\n\nDocument:\n\n- purpose\n- responsibilities\n- future scope\n\nNo executable logic.\n\n---\n\n## relationship_engine.js\n\nPlaceholder only.\n\nDocument intended responsibility.\n\nNo relationship processing.\n\nNo state logic.\n\n---\n\n## state_engine.js\n\nPlaceholder only.\n\nDocument intended responsibility.\n\nNo implementation.\n\n---\n\n## family_engine.js\n\nIMPORTANT\n\nThis is NOT a behavior engine.\n\nThis is NOT a relationship calculator.\n\nThis file is reserved for:\n\nFamily Authority Layer\n\nFuture role:\n\n- Single source of truth for kinship relationships\n- Single source of truth for d