rse`)**: Established as the Active Runtime Canon Repository.\n\n## Freeze \u0026 Rebuild Decision\nWe are starting from absolute zero. Do NOT copy the old repository structure. Do NOT migrate legacy files, worlds, characters, lorebooks, or old engines. Everything must be intentionally reintroduced later through a documented Canon Recovery Workflow.\n\n## Runtime-First Approach\nRuntime behavior overrides documentation. The repository construction hierarchy must follow:\n1. Runtime\n2. Architecture\n3. Workflow\n4. Documentation\n\nBehavior must be preserved before any optimization occurs.\n\n## Future World Reintroduction Policy\nNo archived world, character, engine, lorebook, experience, or storyline may be imported until its canonical form has been verified. Direct imports are forbidden. NotebookLM research must be treated as secondary evidence and cross-verified with the Historical Archive before an approved Canonical Decision allows repository import.\n```\n\n---\n\n### `SvartulfrVerse/core/Architecture.md`\n```markdown\n# Architecture\n\n## Core Principles\n- **Runtime First:** Runtime behavior takes absolute precedence.\n- **Preserve Behavior Before Refactoring:** Legacy behaviors must be accurately preserved before any modernization or optimization.\n- **Knowledge vs Behavior Separation:** Static authority (like family relations) must be isolated from dynamic runtime calculations.\n- **Character Canonicality:** Characters must undergo full audits before implementation.\n- **Incremental Reintroduction:** Introduce systems and characters one at a time.\n- **Canonical Stabilization:** The goal is stabilizing canon, not content expansion or feature bloat.\n\n## Current Scope\n- Only Human\n- Contemporary\n- Los Angeles Dynasty\n\n## Current Canon Assumptions\nThe rebuild is guided by the following dynastic assumptions:\n- **Bloodmoon Dynasty:** Wulfnic Bloodmoon\n- **Douglas Dynasty:** Erik Douglas\n- **Dynastic Union:** Nixara Bloodmoon + Erik Douglas (This union creates the Douglas-Bloodmoon line).\n- **Douglas-Bloodmoon Core Line:** The first-generation heirs of the dynastic union are defined as Malachia Douglas-Bloodmoon, Noah Douglas-Bloodmoon, Jasper Douglas-Bloodmoon, and Alyssa Douglas-Bloodmoon. *(Note: This rule is documented here; no implementation exists yet).*\n\n## Current Validation Paradigm\n**LA_OnlyHuman_Academic_Timeline**\n\n**Principle:** Character age, education, and occupation must form a plausible real-world timeline to prevent migration drift toward unrealistic prodigy careers and preserve contemporary realism.\n\n**Examples:**\n- 19 → Freshman / Sophomore\n- 22-23 → Bachelor Graduate\n- 25 → 3L Law Student / Graduate Student / Early Career Professional\n- 28 → PhD Candidate / Resident / Early Management\n- 31+ → Marriage / Children\n```\n\n---\n\n### `SvartulfrVerse/core/Repository_Scope.md`\n```markdown\n# Repository Scope\n\n## IN SCOPE\nThe following are currently supported and permitted for development:\n- Only Human\n- Contemporary\n- Los Angeles Dynasty\n\n## OUT OF SCOPE\nThe following are explicitly unsupported at this time and must not be implemented:\n- Urban Fantasy\n- Cyber\n- Wasteland\n- Fantasy\n- Norse Mythic\n- Regency\n- Overlay Systems\n- Pack Systems\n- Supernatural Systems\n\n*These elements may be reintroduced later following the Canon Recovery Workflow. Not now.*\n```\n\n---\n\n### `SvartulfrVerse/core/Rebuild_Principles.md`\n```markdown\n# Rebuild Principles\n\n1. **Archive First:** Always reference the Historical Archive (`Progetti`) to verify legacy implementation.\n2. **Runtime Validation Before Expansion:** Stabilize what exists in runtime before adding new features.\n3. **Single Source of Truth:** `SvartulfrVerse` is the ultimate authority. NotebookLM is merely secondary research evidence.\n4. **Preserve Historical Evidence:** Ensure no data is lost in the historical archive during the rebuild.\n5. **No Migration Without Audit:** Required workflow: NotebookLM Discovery 